    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow company's main job is to ensure that the transaction proceeds smoothly and according to the terms of the sale. They're responsible for holding the earnest money, but they also perform various tasks, such as reviewing and processing documents, coordinating communication between parties, and facilitating the exchange of funds. They're like a referee in a game, keeping everything fair and on track. If any issues arise, the escrow company will typically notify the buyer and the seller, and work with them to resolve the problem before the closing date. They might also conduct a final review of the title report and ensure that all outstanding issues are addressed before releasing the funds.",
